# 7. みんなへのプレゼント

Miku: What's keeping Tsukasa? I hope he gets here soon.
Rui: He has some committee business to deal with... However, it shouldn't take up too much of his time, so he should be here soon.
Rin: Oh, Emu☆ What in that box you got there?
Emu: I'm still keeping that a secret☆ I'll open it once everyone's here!
Nene: (That box... It's gotta be her gifts to everyone for Valentine's Day... I wonder what she made...)
Nene: (I also brought my scented candles... I hope they like what I made...)
Nene: (N-No, don't worry...! I thought a lot about them as I made these... So, I'm sure they're going to love them.)
Luka: Oh, Nene, your bag seems awfully heavy today...
Nene: Huh...?! N-No, it isn't... I don't know what you're talking about...
Rui: Hehe. Let's try to wait patiently in the meantime...
Tsukasa: Ah, you've already gathered... I apologize for making you all wait.
KAITO: Not a problem. School business takes priority after all, but the gang's all here now.
Miku: Yeah! Alright, Emu! It's time to show us what's inside your box☆
Emu: Okay☆ Happy Valentine's Day, everyone! Tadaa!!!
Rin: Wow! These dolls are so cute! Wait a second... Are these all made of chocolate...?
Emu: Yup, that's right☆ They're chocolate dolls! But that's not all... Take a look at their faces!
Miku: *Gasp* They... They're us!
Emu: Correctomundo☆ I tried to have them all resemble you guys! So, how'd I do?
KAITO: You did a wonderful job, Emu. And this one must be me... Hehe. It seems like a shame to have to eat it.
Tsukasa: Yes, they're very well made! Thank you, Emu!
Tsukasa: I hope you're looking forward to receiving something spectacular in return for White Day!
Emu: Yay! Thanks! Also, here☆ This is yours, Nene♪
Nene: Oh, okay...
Nene: (Oh, this one... It's like her hair's actually tied off on each side.)
Nene: (And its face... It looks just like me.)
Nene: (Hehe. She must've worked very hard on these to make sure that we liked them...)
Nene: Thanks, Emu...
Emu: You're welcome!
Nene: In return, Emu... Well, for everyone really...
Emu: Hm? What's happening now?
Nene: Um... So...
Nene: I made these for all of you. I hope you like them.
Tsukasa: What?! Wait, you and Emu both made gifts for us?!
Emu: You made these yourself, Nene?! Wow, so many little bags☆ Is this one for me?
Nene: Um, yeah... There's one for everybody. Please take the bag that has your name written on it.
Rui: Let's see... Ah... You made us scented candles?
Len: Scented candles?
Rui: They're candles with scented oils mixed into them. They're designed to release a nice, relaxing fragrance when you light them.
Luka: Oh, that sounds lovely.
MEIKO: Yes, Luka, it's perfect for you! But it's dangerous to leave them lit while you sleep, so please be careful.
Rin: Hey, they're all different colors! That's so cute☆
MEIKO: Oh, you're right! They seem to suit each of us very well.
Len: Wait, hang on... Does that mean...?
Nene: Yeah. I chose colors and fragrances based on the person receiving them.
Rin: Really? Lemme take a sniff... Oh, mine smells like oranges☆
KAITO: Thank you, Nene. These are wonderful!
Nene: Y-You're welcome...! I'm glad to see that you like them so much.
Rui: I didn't realize that you knew how to make something like this, Nene. Did you research how to do this on your own?
Nene: No, I had Mochizuki teach me. I made them with Hoshino... Also, Yoisaki... Remember? She's the one who helped us out during our show the other day.
Rui: Ah... It sounds like this was a wonderful experience for you.
Nene: Y-You think so...?
Nene: (I wasn't sure how my scented candles would turn out at first...)
Nene: (But it gave me a chance to get to know Yoisaki and Mochizuki better... Plus, everyone here seems to really like what I made.)
Nene: (So, I'm really glad that I did this...)
Mizuki: Heh heh heh... The time has finally come... Happy Valentine's Day!
Mizuki: As promised, we brought gifts! And everyone seems to be present.
MEIKO: Why do I need to be here...?
Luka: Why? Because Mizuki and the others said they'd bring gifts for all of us, so we should all be here to accept them.
Mizuki: Yeah. Sorry, but we'll need you to bear with us for a bit.
MEIKO: Alright, fine...
Luka: Hehe. I'm looking forward to seeing what you all brought for us. So, who's going to start us off?
Mizuki: I wanna see what Mafuyu brought. If you don't mind, can you show us?
Mafuyu: Sure. Here...
Ena: Oh, this box! It's from that shop that sells those really fancy chocolates. I heard that they're always sold out...
Mafuyu: I asked some of my classmates about what to get and they suggested these. I had to wait about an hour in line.
Ena: Yeah, that seems pretty normal for this time of year.
Mizuki: But you really went out of your way to get these!
Miku: Thank you, Mafuyu... We really appreciate what you did.
Mafuyu: Then, I'm glad...
Mizuki: Alright, let's move on to our next present-giver...!
Rin: Wow... You all brought so much...
Luka: Mizuki brought cookies that look like different animals, Ena brought chocolates shaped like lollipops...
Mizuki: Heehee! Aren't they cute?
Ena: Hey, don't forget about mine. I worked really hard to get them to look cute by using pink chocolate and colored sugar.
Mizuki: Hmm... Yeah, they do look cute... But I feel like you had ulterior motives...
Mizuki: I mean, you said yourself that they'd look great in selfies and stuff...
Ena: What?! FYI, I'm allowed to use my creations however I like!
Mafuyu: So you did take selfies with them...
Kanade: But it definitely looks like you worked really hard on the wrappers. They have their recipients' names written on them and illustrations to match.
Ena: Yeah, I did. I mean, I wanted everyone to like them.
Ena: Still, Kanade, I think you gave us the biggest surprise this time around...
Kanade: Huh? I did...?
Mizuki: Yeah, totally! I don't think anyone was expecting to receive homemade scented candles from you, Kanade! Not only that...
Miku: They're beautiful...
Mizuki: Yeah, they really are! Plus, each one has a different color and scent!
Ena: And knowing you made them with us in mind, Kanade... I think it makes us all just that much happier.
Ena: That includes you. What do we say when someone does something nice for us...?
Mafuyu: Thank you, Kanade... I'll try using it when I get home.
Kanade: Okay... I'm just glad that you all like them so much.
MEIKO: Len...
Len: Huh...? Y-Yeah?
MEIKO: You haven't said a word this whole time. Is something wrong?
Len: No... Um, so...
Kanade: Len, I believe you have something to tell them...
Rin: What's she talking about...?
Len: U-Umm... The truth is... I also have something for all of you.
Miku: For us...?
Len: Y-Yeah... Kanade taught me how to make scented candles... And we made one together...
Len: And... Here it is... It's only one for all of you...
Mafuyu: ...
Mizuki: What?! L-Len, you also made a candle?! And it looks amazing! It even had flowers in it!
Ena: Yeah... Kanade, you really taught him how to make this?
Ena: Also... I'm seeing sweet peas, roses and all sorts of flowers... They're gorgeous...
Len: So... Kanade helped me pick out flowers that suited each of you...
Len: She also helped me choose the color and fragrance.
Miku: I had no idea... Thank you, Len. You too, Kanade.
Len: Y-You're welcome...!
Rin: Hey, it smells like apples...
Len: Oh, actually... It's chamomile.
Luka: Oh, Len, which flower did you pick for me...?
Len: Um, yours is...
Kanade: Good for you, Len...
Len: Th-Thanks...!
Len: I really appreciate what you did for me, Kanade...
Len: You helped make this Valentine's Day feel really special...!
Kanade: No... I should be the one thanking you.
Len: Huh?
Kanade: You made me realize something important.
Kanade: I had a lot of fun making these scented candles with you and the others.
